<div class="comments-body czajnik"> 
<p>Have you tried any distributed source control? I&#39;ve recently switched from Subversion to Mercurial, and I&#39;m very happy about the change. </p>

<p>The most important reason was the ability to clone the repository to my laptop, do some checkins there (without network access, on a plain, train, etc.) and resync with just one command when I&#39;m back home. Distributed model seems cool even for a single developer :)</p>

<p>Also I don&#39;t like the way Subversion deals with branches and tags (i.e. by &quot;cheap copy&quot;). It simply doesn&#39;t work well for me, e.g. if one checkouts a repository with many tagged and branched versions, the workspace becomes much bigger than it should be. To avoid it, one needs to selectively checkout parts of the repository, I find it quite annoying. <br />
</p>
